The paper proposes a semantic segmentation approach for compound figure separation, which involves image processing and information retrieval. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV), information retrieval (cs.IR), and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes an anchor-based master image detection algorithm, which involves deep learning techniques, making it relevant to the deep learning (cs.DL) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
